column168: DARREL BRAMHALL, DRIVER FOR CKC INC., WAS DRIVING EAST ON I-10 IN A TRUCK & TRAILER ROLL-OFF VEHICLE. APPROXIMATELY 20 MILES EAST OF PHOENIX, AZ. THE TRAILER DRIFTED ONTO THE RIGHT SHOULDER OF THE HIGHWAY. THE FRONT RIGHT OUT SIDE TIRE HIT AN OBSTRUCTION, CAUSING THE TIRE BLOW OUT AS WELL AS BREAKING THE WHEEL. DRIVER WAS UNABLE TO CONTROL THE TRAILER WHICH ROLLED AND BROKE THE HITCH OFF THE TRUCK. TRAILER LANDED ON IT'S SIDE AND BROKE THE CHAIN H OLDING THE ROLLING-ROOF CLOSED. WHEN THE CHAIN BROKE, THE LID SLID OPEN AND ALLOWED APPROXIMATLY 8 YDS OF THE 12 YD. SHIPMENT TO SPILL ON THE GROUND. THE ARIZONA HIGHWAY PATROL ARRIVED ON THE SCENE AND ARRANGEMENTS WERE MADE FOR THE CLEAN-UP DISPOSAL CONTROL SERVICE WAS CALLED TO SUPERVISE THE OPERA TION. THE ENTIRE SPILL WAS CLEANED UP IN A MATTER OF HOURS. THERE WERE NO I NJURIES AND NO OTHER VEHICLES INVOLVED IN THE ACCIDENT. THE DAMAGE TO THE T RAILER AND CONTAINER WERE MINIMAL. BOTH WERE BACK IN OPERATION THE FOLLOWIN G DAY. CKC INC. IS TRYING TO DEVELOP A STURDIER WAY TO LATCH THE ROLLING-RO OFS ON THE CONTAINERS. HAD THE CHAIN NOT BROKEN, NO MATERIAL WOULD HAVE ESC APED. IN ADDITION TO THE 8 YDS OF MATERIAL SPILLED AND ADDITIONAL 14 YDS. O F SOIL WAS TAKEN TO INSURE A TOTAL CLEAN-UP. THIS 22 YDS OF MATERIAL IS SCH EDULED TO BE DISPOSED OF CHEMICAL WASTE MANAGEMENT-0KETTLEMAN HILLS FACILIT Y IN CALIFORNIA.
